org.processmining.xesalignmentextension

Class XAlignmentExtension

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.deckfour.xes.extension.XExtension
      • org.processmining.xesalignmentextension.XAlignmentExtension
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class XAlignmentExtension
extends org.deckfour.xes.extension.XExtension
    This extension allows to store an event log that has been aligned to some model. It defines nine attributes:
    • alignment:modelid -
    • alignment:fitness
    • alignment:penaltycost - Not yet implementet
    • alignment:likelihoodcost - Not yet implemented
    • alignment:movetype -
    • alignment:modelmove - label of the activity (might be ambiguous)
    • alignment:logmove - label of the event (might be ambiguous)
    • alignment:activityid - unique id of the activity
    • alignment:eventclassid - unique class of the event
    • alignment:observable -
    Author:
    F. Mannhardt (f.mannhardt@tue.nl)
